Tha '''Dà-Spioraideach''' 'na facal air [[treas seòrsa|treas seòrsaich]] (mar eisimpleir, bean maireann ri fear) a bheil am measg mòran, mur eil sa' chuid as motha, nam cinneadh [[Ameireaganach Dùthchasach]]. 'S àbhaisd dhi a' bhith a' toirt iomradh air spiorad fireannta agus spiorad boireanta 'maireann sa' chorp cheudna. 'S i air chleachdadh le Ameireaganaich Dhùthchasach [[co-sheòrsachd|co-sheòrsach]], [[leasbach]], [[dà-mhiannachd|dà-mhiannach]], [[thairis-sheòrsachd|thairis-sheòrsach]], agus [[eadar-sheòrsachd|eadar-sheòrsach]] a thoirt dealbh orra fhèin. There are also native terms for these individuals in the various sa' chànanan eugsamhaile nan Ameireaganach Dùthchasach.

Tha 'n facal sean "''berdache''" (às an [[Fraingis|Fhraingis]] ''bardache'', às an [[Spàinnis]] ''bardaxa'' no ''bardaje''/''bardaja'', às an [[Eadailtis]] ''bardasso'' no ''berdasia'', às an [[Arabais]] ''bardaj'', às an [[Persiais]] ''bardaj'' no ''barah'' ciallachadh "gille air chumail," no "fear-siùrsach") 'na fhacal gnèitheach air chleachdadh gu h-àraid le luchd-corpeòlas agus diùltaidh Ameireaganach Dùthchasach an facal gu tric seach tha iad ga thuigsinn ri mì-dhòigheil agus cronail. Tha e gu leathann air chur nì an àite le ''Dà-Spioraideach''.

These individuals are often viewed as having two spirits occupying one body.  Their dress is usually a mixture of traditionally male and traditionally female articles.  They have distinct gender and social roles in their tribes.  For instance, among the [[Lakota]] there was one ceremony fad an [[Dannsa na Grèine]] that was performed only by a two-spirited person of that tribe. (Seallaibh [[winkte]](uingte))

